description: After a video of a vada pav seller being 'arrested' by police officials went viral on social media, Delhi police on Saturday responded to the videos, saying that the woman was not arrested, and no case has been registered against her.
title: 'Vada Pav' girl not arrested, no case registered: Police on video

description: Seventy-five international delegates from Election Management Bodies (EMBs) of 23 countries are visiting India to observe the country's national elections, as announced by the Election Commission. The program, starting on May 4, aims to familiarize the visitors with India's electoral system and best practices. The program will conclude on May 9, 2024.
title: 75 delegates from 23 countries arrive to observe LS elections

description: Since entrusting Joginder Sharma with the decisive over of the 2007 T20 World Cup final against Pakistan, former CSK and India skipper MS Dhoni has built a reputation for instilling confidence in young talents, transforming them into champions. Dhoni's faith in youth was evident when he passed on the CSK captaincy to Ruturaj Gaikwad before IPL 2024.
title: Watch: 'In my cricket life, Dhoni plays my father's role'

description: Tatiparthi Jeevan Reddy, a prominent Congress figure and candidate for the Nizamabad Lok Sabha seat, became embroiled in controversy after reportedly slapping a woman who indicated her intention to vote for the 'flower' symbol in the upcoming May 13 election.
title: Congress pick slaps woman for saying voting for 'flower' symbol
'Killer nurse' in US sentenced to 380-760 years for murdering 17 patients

description: Mitchell Starc reflects on IPL's impact player rule, highlighting potential effects on T20 World Cup strategies. Emphasizes current focus on KKR's success over long-term international cricket goals, utilizing IPL for World Cup readiness. Teams have been batting with greater boldness and fearlessness since the impact player rule was introduced last year, which has resulted in totals that routinely surpass 200.
title: IPL 2024: Mitchell Starc feels Impact Player rule changes...

description: Meta employees call out company censorship of Palestinian support, demanding transparency, acknowledgment, and end to censorship. They urge leadership to issue a statement for a Gaza ceasefire, seeking inclusivity and accountability.
title: Palestine posts ban: Meta employees send letter to CEO Zuckerberg

description: Mumbai Indians' eighth loss in 11 games has all but put an end to the Hardik Pandya-led team. Their 24-run defeat against KKR, in which Rohit was an impact substitute, saw him score just 11 runs in 12 balls in the second innings. This loss almost saw the five-time winners eliminated from the IPL this year.
title: Why Rohit Sharma played as an impact sub against Kolkata Knight Riders

description: Rajinikanth reunites with Amitabh Bachchan after 34 years for 'Vettaiyan'. Directed by TJ Gnanavel, the film's photos on social media created buzz. The movie boasts a stellar cast and music by Anirudh Ravichander.
title: Amitabh Bachchan on working with Rajinikanth: Greater joy

description: In Gujarat politics, diverse individuals like Suman Khushwah, Nisar Shaikh, Vedu Sirasat, Mahesh Thakor, and Faruk Chauhan contest elections for various reasons, ranging from justice quests to civic empowerment, showcasing the power of perseverance and pursuit of equality.
title: David vs Goliath: Underdogs brave battlefield in Gujarat

description: Raj Babbar's political journey started in 1994 when he received a 'lightning call' from Mulayam Singh Yadav. Over the years, he transitioned from being a star campaigner to a seasoned politician, winning and losing in various elections.
title: Raj Babbar returns to stage; can he be Gurgaon’s aaj ki awaaz?

description: Indian-American groups oppose the display of a separatist Kashmiri flag at Rutgers University, citing inappropriate messaging in the midst of turmoil over Israel's actions in Gaza. Conflict, casualties, and demands intensify the situation.
title: 'Do not allow display of Kashmiri separatist flag'

description: In Bijnor, a teacher was shot by an ex-student after rejecting his 'friendship' proposal. The incident occurred during class, witnessed by 25 students. The teacher, Komal, is in critical condition at a Meerut hospital.
title: Man, 21, shoots at teacher for rejecting 'friendship' in UP's Bijnor

description: Elvish Yadav faced money laundering accusations linked to a snake venom case. He spent time in custody but later got bail. The chargesheet detailed snake smuggling and venom use at parties, with police later withdrawing some charges.
title: Snake venom case: ED accuses Elvish Yadav of money laundering

description: On Saturday, the government lifted the prohibition on onion exports, providing significant relief to traders in Maharashtra. This decision coincides with the upcoming phases of the Lok Sabha election, particularly in the onion-producing regions of Maharashtra. The Director General of Foreign Trade (DGFT) specified a Minimum Export Price (MEP) for onions at $550 per tonne in a notification.
title: Govt lifts ban on onion exports before polls in Maharashtra

description: Russian chess legend Garry Kasparov's jest about Indian politics sparked online buzz. Playfully responding to Congress MP Rahul Gandhi's claim of being India's top politician-chess player, Kasparov quipped, "First win Rae Bareli before challenging for the top." Despite clarifying it as a joke, his comment ignited a lively discourse on social media, blending humour with politics in unexpected ways.
title: Garry Kasparov clarifies 'little joke' on Rahul Gandhi
Tesla urges investors to get Elon Musk his $47 billion pay package

description: Apple introduced Precision Finding for iPhone 15 series users, available in select countries. An ad features a Mandalorian at a convention center. Apple announced a Let Loose event for new iPad models.
title: Apple’s Star Wars-themed ad promoting iPhone's ‘find your friends’

description: Delhi CEO's office approved the Lok Sabha elections campaign song of AAP after the party made changes following Election Commission guidelines. AAP's campaign song 'Jail ka Jawab Vote se Denge' was initially claimed to be banned but was approved after modifications.
title: AAP campaign song gets approval from poll body

description: Both Gujarat Titans and Royal Challengers Bengaluru have had a forgettable season. RCB are rock bottom of the 10-team table with just three wins in 10 matches and Gujarat Titans have done only a shade better at No. 8 with four wins in 10 matches. Kohli is currently No. 2 in the list of run-getters this season with 500 runs in 10 matches,
title: Watch: When Gill met Virat - 'Badi jaldi aaya practice pe'

description: Congress faces internal conflicts as contenders vie for Lingayat representation, impacting party unity and potential election outcomes. Lingayat community support pivotal for Congress' success in upcoming polls.
title: Infighting among its Lingayats a challenge for Congress in K'taka

description: Complainants in Rohith Vemula case demand justice, challenge police closure, and seek caste certificate. They face rejection and job loss, planning to fight for justice despite political motives and societal stigma. Vijay Kumar emphasizes real reasons over caste discussions and questions police authority.
title: Who killed our friend Vemula? Complainants in suicide case

description: Sucharita Mohanty withdrew from contesting the Puri Lok Sabha seat due to inadequate financial support from Congress. BJD's Arup Patnaik and BJP's Sambit Patra have filed nominations for the upcoming election.
title: No funding from Congress, Puri Lok Sabha nominee returns ticket

description: Rahul Gandhi succeeds Sonia Gandhi in Rae Bareli, continuing the family's political legacy. The lineage spans generations, with Feroze Gandhi and Indira Gandhi also representing the constituency. Similar trends are seen in other constituencies.
title: UP seats where poll baton has passed on to next generation

description: It was just the fourth instance in IPL history where both the teams got bowled out -- another statistic that highlights the batting-friendly conditions in the IPL since its inception in 2008. After the 2018 season, it was the first instance of 20 wickets falling in an IPL match. KKR won by 24 runs to virtually eliminate MI from the race to playoffs.
title: MI vs KKR: Finally a bowlers' match in IPL 2024 that saw...

description: Villagers in Nandri village, Dausa district, reacted violently to the alleged rape and murder of a pregnant woman, resulting in clashes with the police. The suspect's house was burnt, relatives' houses attacked, and suspects detained.
title: Villagers in Rajasthan set rape-murder accused's house on fire

description: Hassan MP Prajwal Revanna faces rape allegations after threats with a gun. Charges include sexual harassment and stalking. The case involves accusations of abduction and involvement in sleaze videos. Police are investigating the criminal case.
title: 'Revanna raped me after threatening to shoot me, hubby'

description: Thansen K, a double-hand amputee, obtained a driving licence in Tamil Nadu after impressing doctors with his driving skills using stumps. His story of overcoming challenges inspires others with disabilities to achieve independence.
title: Man, 30, without hands gets 4-wheeler licence in Chennai

description: Mitchell Starc, the player for whom KKR splurged a whopping Rs 24.75 crore at the IPL auction, making him the most expensive purchase in IPL history, finally justified his hefty price tag. He delivered a match-winning spell of 4/33, leading Kolkata to a 24-run victory despite posting a below-par score of 169 on the board.
title: 'Khatarnak team!' - KKR get hungrier for third IPL title

description: Mumbai Indians are virtually eliminated from contention for the IPL 2024 playoffs. This season has been one of their most challenging in IPL history. Hardik Pandya and his team suffered their eighth loss in 11 matches, succumbing to the Kolkata Knight Riders by 24 runs at their home turf, the Wankhede Stadium, on Friday.
title: 'Mumbai Indians ki kahani khatam': What went wrong for Hardik & Co

description: May 4th hosts a myriad of historic events, from the birth of the Royal Canadian Navy to Latvia's declaration of independence. It's marked by International Firefighters' Day and Star Wars Day, along with notable birthdays and achievements in space exploration. Each event signifies significant milestones in cultural, political, and scientific realms, contributing to the day's historical legacy.
title: Interesting facts about today

description: Joshimath study by geologists emphasized monitoring ground deformation and weather parameters for landslide hazard mitigation. It revealed increased landslide velocity due to extreme rain events, stressing the importance of systematic monitoring.
title: Alarming rise in landslide velocity in Joshimath: Study
